辅导员
辅导员 (class counselor) assists students in fulfilling needs like acquiring pet food when the cafeteria cannot accommodate requests.<SEP>辅导员 (class counselor) provides assistance for students needing help with requests like pet food procurement.

宠物食品
Pet food is the product category in question, which the食堂 cannot manufacture.<SEP>Pet food is the specific category of product the食堂 cannot manufacture, prompting alternative procurement methods.

网购
Online shopping represents a recommended method for obtaining unavailable items like pet food through digital marketplaces.

老师
老师作为学院成员，在食堂政策下享有自由选择餐品的权利，但若强制指定打饭地点则违反规定并需被举报。<SEP>老师是被允许在本食堂就餐的教职员工类别

督察队
督察队是一个负责监督或检查的组织，根据规定不能在食堂就餐

校长
校长是学校负责人，按规则不允许在食堂就餐且其进入会触发他人离开指令

学院食堂
A college dining hall where multiple food service brands operate under safety oversight.<SEP>A dining hall within a college campus offering multiple brands, where operational status and health safety of the brands must be monitored.<SEP>学院食堂是学院内自选制的餐饮设施，允许师生自由选择餐品品牌，并明确规定不得强制限制饮食选择。

督察部
督察部是学院内的监督部门，负责处理违反规定的行为，如有人被强制指定打饭地点时可联系其寻求帮助。<SEP>督察部负责监督学院政策执行，处理违规行为（如强制指定打饭地点），并为受侵害权益的学生提供帮助。<SEP>督察部是负责处理食堂内动物出现事件的学生管理部门，承担报告和处置职责<SEP>督察部负责处理在食堂内发现动物情况的学生部门。

学生会
学生会在文本中涉及组织行为，若其人员强制要求前往特定位置用餐，则构成违规需通过督察部解决。<SEP>学生会在文本中涉及组织行为，若其人员强制要求前往特定位置用餐，则构成违规，需拒绝并联系督察部。

同学
学生是食堂服务的主要使用者，受政策保护可自由选择餐食，并有权在遭遇违规行为时向督察部求助。

指定位置打饭事件
该事件指学生或教师被强制要求前往特定地点用餐的违反自选制的行为，需通过督察部处理。

餐饮自由选择政策
学院食堂的核心政策，保障师生自主选择餐品的权利并禁止任何形式的强制限制。

学生/同学
Student group instructed to check brand health reports and report abnormalities as per guidelines.<SEP>Students instructed to monitor brand operations, check health reports, and report violations to the Supervision Department.

品牌
Different food service providers operating within the college canteen, which may temporarily suspend or reopen operations.<SEP>Individual food service providers operating within the college canteen that may temporarily suspend or resume operations.

品牌重新恢复工作
Event when a brand that has been suspended for over a month resumes operations, triggering health inspections and oversight procedures.<SEP>Event where a food service brand resumes operations after being closed for over a month, requiring re-inspection and validation.

卫生表
Health inspection reports signed by the Supervision Department to confirm brand compliance with safety standards.

食堂
The Dining Hall is a facility within the Academy that provides food services and issues guidelines to students.<SEP>The cafeteria advises contacting the class counselor to help address needs that it cannot fulfill directly.<SEP>The cafeteria directs users to contact the counselor as an alternative when they cannot fulfill requests for pet food.<SEP>食堂是指发生动物出现的餐饮场所，需要遵守安全指引的地理区域

发现猫或狗在食堂
该事件指在食堂内检测到猫或狗的存在，触发紧急处置程序

卫生
涉及公共卫生和环境清洁的规范要求，在动物出现时需要特别维护

督察部同学
负责在食堂发现动物事件时执行汇报和处置工作的学生工作人员

就餐安全
涉及因食品安全威胁而采取的应急措施类别，如暂停用餐等强制性行为指导<SEP>涉及因食品安全隐患而暂停用餐的安全措施类别，如动物出现时的应对流程

1-4号宿舍楼
Dormitory buildings numbered 1 to 4 where the canteen provides delivery service.<SEP>Dormitory buildings numbered 1 to 4, designated as the only locations where takeout is delivered.

外卖服务
Takeout delivery service provided by the campus canteen with strict location restrictions.<SEP>Takeout delivery service provided by the campus canteen, limited to specific dormitory locations.

食堂自取服务
Self-pickup service at the canteen for orders placed outside designated dormitory areas.<SEP>Self-pickup service available at the canteen for orders not delivered to approved dormitories.

外卖配送政策
Policy enforced by the campus canteen restricting takeout delivery to specific dormitories and requiring self-pickup otherwise.

学生守则
Student Code of Conduct is a set of institutional rules outlining expected student behavior, including restrictions on where food can be consumed.<SEP>Student Code of Conduct outlines rules students must follow to ensure orderly operations within the academy.

食堂建议
Dining Hall Notice is an official announcement prohibiting students from eating in classrooms to uphold campus cleanliness and policy compliance.<SEP>Dining Hall Notice is an official communication from the Academy instructing students not to consume food in classrooms.
